# DRAFT FOR ANALYST REVIEW — CVE-2026-0280 PAN-OS IPv6 Firewall Policy Bypass
#
# ⚠️  SEVERITY DISCREPANCY — analysts must adjudicate before acting on priority:
#     [1] NVD scores this CVSS 7.2 (HIGH)
#     [3] CVE.org CNA-published record scores this CVSS v4.0 1.7 (LOW)
#     The gap is substantial; confirm the authoritative vendor score at [2]
#     before treating this as HIGH priority.
#
# Confidence: No public PoC known — pattern inferred from the CVE/advisory
# description only [2]. The description indicates exploitation requires
# crafted IPv6 packets that cause the PAN-OS dataplane to misprocess headers
# and bypass security policy evaluation.
#
# No packet-capture (PCAP) data source is available to this pipeline —
# this pattern is NOT verified against captured exploit traffic.
#
# Detection rationale: The advisory describes crafted IPv6 packets targeting
# PAN-OS management/dataplane interfaces. This rule alerts on IPv6 traffic
# carrying extension headers (indicated by Next Header values other than
# common upper-layer protocols) directed at typical PAN-OS management and
# data-plane service ports. IPv6 extension headers (Hop-by-Hop 0x00,
# Routing 0x2B, Destination Options 0x3C, Fragment 0x2C) are a common
# mechanism for crafting packets that confuse stateful inspection engines.
# Because no PoC or PCAP is available, the byte-level pattern below targets
# extension-header presence in raw IPv6 traffic and should be considered
# LOW-CONFIDENCE. A high false-positive rate is expected. Analyst tuning
# is strongly recommended before any blocking action.
#
# Limitations:
#  - Without PoC or PCAP, the exact header manipulation method is unknown.
#  - This rule cannot distinguish malicious crafted IPv6 from legitimate
#    extension-header usage (e.g., MIPv6, SRv6 deployments).
#  - If PAN-OS management is not exposed on $HOME_NET, adjust destination
#    to the specific management interface subnet.
#  - RCE classification from the CVE record [1] is noted, but the advisory
#    [2] describes a firewall bypass, not direct code execution — confirm
#    whether RCE is a downstream consequence of reaching a protected service.

alert ip $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET any (
  msg:"THREATFORGE CVE-2026-0280 PAN-OS IPv6 Firewall Policy Bypass crafted extension header";
  ip_proto:ipv6;
  flow:stateless;
  byte_test:1,&,0xF0,0,relative,big-endian;
  pcre:"/^\x60[\x00-\xff]{3}[\x00-\xff]{2}(?:\x00|\x2b|\x2c|\x3c)[\x00-\xff]/";
  threshold:type both, track by_src, count 10, seconds 60;
  reference:cve,2026-0280;
  metadata:mitre_technique_id T1190, is_kev false, status experimental;
  classtype:attempted-bypass; sid:9000280; rev:1; )

